{
  "answer": "**The Consequence of Apostasy**\nApostasy is strictly addressed in the traditions, with an authentic narration in Sahih al-Bukhari recording the Prophet's explicit command: \"If somebody (a Muslim) discards his religion, kill him\" [1]. \n\n**Abandoning Prayer as Disbelief**\nThe complete abandonment of the daily prayer is directly classified as an act of absolute disbelief in Sahih Muslim. The Prophet explicitly stated, \"Verily between man and between polytheism and unbelief is the negligence of prayer\" [2]. This is corroborated by another narration which affirms that the dividing line \"Between man and polytheism and unbelief is the abandonment of salat\" [3].",
  "conversation_id": "b75c54d4-0ca8-4686-8f68-eef116d359e6",
